nodes.title: Notes on IPA & FaceID
widgets_values:
Settings can be freely tampred with as there is nothing that can really break the workflow in these nodes.

Load Face Image
----------------

As it says this is where a decent picture of teh face you want to use goes.



Unified Loader & FaceID
------------------------

Settings should be good for most cases.

In the Files Download available on CivitAI.
(https://civitai.com/models/428894)

All the files have been provided for:
 - FACEIDE PLUS - SD1.5 only
 and
 - FACEID PLUS V2

Other preset versions can be found at (https://github.com/cubiq/ComfyUI_IPAdapter_plus)



Face Preview
-------------

Is there more for troubleshooting if results are not as planned.

nodes.title: Notes on Image Generation
widgets_values:
This is a basic Image Generation Workflow feel free to tamper with the settings to your hearts content.

SD1.5, SDXL and PonyXL based models are able to be used with this Workflow.



Load Checkpoint (Adv.)
-----------------------

Has been outfitted with an internal Anything Everywhere Node that broadcasts the Baked in VAE to all open VAE pipes in the Workflow. If you use a model that doesn't have a Baked in VAE you'll have to couple a Load VAE into those pipes yourself.


Empty Latent Image (Adv.)
--------------------------

Has been outfitted with a Size Select Function. If you want to use a different size feel free to alter manual_width and height parameters.



hiresfixScale
--------------

This requires an ESRGAN based upscaler Model.

nodes.title: Notes on the ControlNet
widgets_values:
All this does is use a Posture Image to create a Depth Map and uses that to make your prompt image Character use the same Posture. Overall the settings should not be toouched.



Load Image (ControlNet)
------------------------
Has been outfitted with Depth Map and OpenPose Outputs. all additional settings are there to be tampered with and should not break the Workflow.



Depth Map & OpenPose Preview
-----------------------------

Are there for the purpose of troubleshooting and finetuning the Pre-Processor Settings.



Advanced Info
--------------

If you Bypass the FaceID group and OpenPose nodes you can use this for Landscape pictures as well then the Depth Map will function as a Guide for how your landscape picture will look.

YAY DOUBLE FUNCTIONS!!!
